{
  "texts": [
    "Visualization techniques such as bivariate choropleth maps, map pixelation, Q-Q plots, and glyph rotation to represent spatial predictions with uncertainty can be used 162.",
    "One the model level, two primary groups of approaches to reduce uncertainty could be selected: those related to Gaussian Process Modeling and those associated with ensemble modeling.",
    "Gaussian Process Regression, also known as kriging, is commonly used for UQ in geospatial applications, providing a natural way to estimate the uncertainty associated with spatial predictions 163.",
    "Another approach, known as Lower Upper Bound Estimation, was applied to estimate sediment load prediction intervals generated by neural networks 164.",
    "For soil organic mapping, researchers compared different methods, including sequential Gaussian simulation (SGS), quantile regression forest (QRF), universal kriging, and kriging coupled with random forest."
  ]
}